					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>301 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>330</height>
										<width>245</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>205</height>
										<width>150</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>301 folios (+ 3 modern paper flyleaves and 1 older paper flyleaf at the beginning and at the end), one unfoliated leaf [folio 251*] after folio 251.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>37 quires: i10 (folios 1-10), ii8 (folios 11-18), iii8 (folios 19-26), iv8 (folios 27-34), v8 (folios 35-42), vi8 (folios 43-50), vii8 (folios 51-58), viii8 (folios 59-66), ix8 (folios 67-74), x8 (folios 75-82), xi8 (folios 83-90), xii8 (folios 91-98), xiii8 (folios 99-107), xiv8 (folios 108-114), xv8 (folios 115-122), xvi8 (folios 123-130), xvii8 (folios 131-138), xviii8 (folios 139-146), xix8 (folios 147-154), xx8 (folios 155-162), xxi8 (folios 163-170), xxii8 (folios 171-178), xxiii8 (folios 179-186), xiv10 (folios 187-196), xxv8 (folios 197-204), xxvi8 (folios 205-212), xxvii8 (folios 213-220), xxviii8 (folios 221-228), xxix8 (folios 229-236), xxx8 (folios 237-244), xxxi8 (folios 245-251), xxxii8 (folios 252-259), xxxiii8 (folios 260-267), xxxiv8 (folios 268-275), xxxv8 (folios 276-283), xxxvi8 (folios 284-291), xxxvii10 (folios 292-301).</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="36" writtenLines="36">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible ruling with a sharp object (complete). Hair-side and flesh-side are distinguishable.
</p>
									<p>Scant marginal notes. </p>
									<p>Fore edge, lower and upper edges are colored with red strips.
</p>
									<p>From folio 32 parallel Hebrew foliation starting with no. 22. </p>
									<p>The older paper flyleaves of the binding have watermarks similar to <ref target="Heawood_1950" type="number">2745</ref>.
Erasures by a censor (e.g. on folios 38r, 54v, 55r, 264v, 266r, 272v).</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square script, unpunctuated (except a passage on folio 139r), of the 15th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Shelomoh ibn Alzuḳ</name> : inscribed in the colophon, volume II, folio 434v.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="censor">Fra Giro[lamo] de Durazzano de Predi[?]</name>: censor's signature and note <date calendar="Gregorian">1640 </date>(folio 1r). Erasures (e.g. folios 58v-59r, 96r-v, 272v). (Narkiss reads the name Durallano), on him see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="number">89</ref>.
</p>
							<p>Two illegible Hebrew notes (folio 1r).
</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Bernard Mould</name> (b. c. 1683; d. 1744), chaplain at Smyrna: inscribed with his name, <name type="place">Smyrna</name>, <date calendar="Gregorian">1724 </date>(folio 301r); sold to <name type="person" role="owner">Edward Harley</name> on <date calendar="Gregorian">28 July 1725</date> (see <ref target="Wright_1972"/>).</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house. </p>
								<p>Spine title: 'Moses ben Maimon. Mishneh Torah. Hebrew. Vol. I. Brit. Mus. Harley 5698.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
